1018
IT employees




$70.9MEST.
IT Budget




Sage Group is a British enterprise software company. Sage products include enterprise resource planning (ERP) software, payment solutions, and cloud-based software as a service (SaaS) products for its clients who are based worldwide.

Procurement Process:
IT and technology sourcing is managed by… MoreSage Group is a British enterprise software company. Sage products include enterprise resource planning (ERP) software, payment solutions, and cloud-based software as a service (SaaS) products for its clients who are based worldwide.

Procurement Process:
IT and technology sourcing is managed by the company's procurement department.
2016

IT Structure:
The IT department is manged via a global structure, with a functional alignment and regional and location management levels. 

2013 and previously: 

IT Priorities:
• In 2013, Sage is continuing its virtualization efforts as well as putting an emphasis on… More2016

IT Structure:
The IT department is manged via a global structure, with a functional alignment and regional and location management levels. 

2013 and previously: 

IT Priorities:
• In 2013, Sage is continuing its virtualization efforts as well as putting an emphasis on its storage area network (SAN) and its technical architecture.

IT Structure

• Sage Group's IS department handles operations for information security, enterprise development, and IT operations.  
• The company's Chief Technology Officer oversees the company's research and development operations, which is primarily applications-focused.  
• Sage's Pay subsidiary also has an internal IT division of its own, with an IT security team.
• Sage's North American unit, as well as Sage Payment Solutions, which are subsidiaries of Sage Group are on RainKing as separate profiles. Please note that the profiles for Sage Hospitality Resources, LLC and Sage Products are separate companies and are not part of Sage Group.

IT Bytes

• Given the nature of Sage's business as an enterprise resource planning (ERP) software company, it uses its own application for that purpose. 
• Sage uses HP Blade servers in its data centers which are virtualized using VMware solutions. 
• Company networks are constructed with Cisco hardware. 
• The company allows employees to use BlackBerry, Apple, and Android mobile devices.





